# Project Skills

Skills live in `.cursor/skills/`. Load a skill's `SKILL.md` when its description matches the task.

## How to use

1. When a task matches a skill's description, read that skill's `SKILL.md` first.
2. Load only the referenced docs needed for the current subtask.
3. Do not modify skill files.

## Entry points

| Task | Start here |
|------|------------|
| SpacetimeDB (any) | `.cursor/skills/spacetimedb/SKILL.md` |
| TypeScript server module | `.cursor/skills/spacetimedb-client-typescript/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/rules/typescript-server.mdc` |
| TypeScript/React client | `.cursor/skills/spacetimedb-client-typescript/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/rules/typescript-client.mdc` |
| CLI commands | `.cursor/skills/spacetimedb-cli/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/rules/cli.mdc` |
| Three.js / R3F scene work | `.cursor/skills/r3f-fundamentals/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/skills/threejs-fundamentals/SKILL.md` |
| Game systems / ECS | `.cursor/skills/game-systems/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/skills/ecs/SKILL.md` |
